item.title: On Manipulating Signals of User-Item Graph: A Jacobi Polynomial-based Graph Collaborative Filtering
item.description: Graph CF has attracted more and more attention in recent years due to its effectiveness in leveraging high-order information in the user-item bipartite graph for better recommendations.

item.title: Conditional Diffusion Models for Weakly Supervised Medical Image Segmentation
item.description: Recent advances in denoising diffusion probabilistic models have shown great success in image synthesis tasks.

item.title: BioBLP: A Modular Framework for Learning on Multimodal Biomedical Knowledge Graphs
item.description: We train models using a biomedical KG containing approximately 2 million triples, and evaluate the performance of the resulting entity embeddings on the tasks of link prediction, and drug-protein interaction prediction, comparing against methods that do not take attribute data into account.

item.title: FinRED: A Dataset for Relation Extraction in Financial Domain
item.description: Relation extraction models trained on a source domain cannot be applied on a different target domain due to the mismatch between relation sets.

item.title: SciLit: A Platform for Joint Scientific Literature Discovery, Summarization and Citation Generation
item.description: We propose SciLit, a pipeline that automatically recommends relevant papers, extracts highlights, and suggests a reference sentence as a citation of a paper, taking into consideration the user-provided context and keywords.

item.title: CUE: An Uncertainty Interpretation Framework for Text Classifiers Built on Pre-Trained Language Models
item.description: We then generate text representations by perturbing the latent space which causes fluctuation in predictive uncertainty.

item.title: Financial Numeric Extreme Labelling: A Dataset and Benchmarking for XBRL Tagging
item.description: The U. S. Securities and Exchange Commission (SEC) mandates all public companies to file periodic financial statements that should contain numerals annotated with a particular label from a taxonomy.

item.title: Fine-grained Expressivity of Graph Neural Networks
item.description: In particular, we characterize the expressive power of MPNNs in terms of the tree distance, which is a graph distance based on the concepts of fractional isomorphisms, and substructure counts via tree homomorphisms, showing that these concepts have the same expressive power as the $1$-WL and MPNNs on graphons.

item.title: Mildly Constrained Evaluation Policy for Offline Reinforcement Learning
item.description: Offline reinforcement learning (RL) methodologies enforce constraints on the policy to adhere closely to the behavior policy, thereby stabilizing value learning and mitigating the selection of out-of-distribution (OOD) actions during test time.

item.title: Mutual Information Regularization for Weakly-supervised RGB-D Salient Object Detection
item.description: In particular, following the principle of disentangled representation learning, we introduce a mutual information upper bound with a mutual information minimization regularizer to encourage the disentangled representation of each modality for salient object detection.

item.title: Enabling Efficient Interaction between an Algorithm Agent and an LLM: A Reinforcement Learning Approach
item.description: Experimental results also suggest that by learning a mediator model to interact with the LLM, the agent's performance becomes more robust against both exploratory and stochastic environments.

item.title: On Pitfalls of Test-Time Adaptation
item.description: Test-Time Adaptation (TTA) has recently emerged as a promising approach for tackling the robustness challenge under distribution shifts.

item.title: A Functional Data Perspective and Baseline On Multi-Layer Out-of-Distribution Detection
item.description: A key feature of out-of-distribution (OOD) detection is to exploit a trained neural network by extracting statistical patterns and relationships through the multi-layer classifier to detect shifts in the expected input data distribution.

item.title: Exploring the effects of robotic design on learning and neural control
item.description: Overall, this dissertation intimates the ability to automatically design robots that are more general purpose than current robots and that can perform various tasks while requiring less computation.

item.title: Instructive Feature Enhancement for Dichotomous Medical Image Segmentation
item.description: Deep neural networks have been widely applied in dichotomous medical image segmentation (DMIS) of many anatomical structures in several modalities, achieving promising performance.

item.title: Human-imperceptible, Machine-recognizable Images
item.description: Massive human-related data is collected to train neural networks for computer vision tasks.

item.title: Exploring Model Dynamics for Accumulative Poisoning Discovery
item.description: In this paper, we dive into the perspective of model dynamics and propose a novel information measure, namely, Memorization Discrepancy, to explore the defense via the model-level information.

item.title: Bayesian post-hoc regularization of random forests
item.description: Random Forests are powerful ensemble learning algorithms widely used in various machine learning tasks.

item.title: Learning to Do or Learning While Doing: Reinforcement Learning and Bayesian Optimisation for Online Continuous Tuning
item.description: Online tuning of real-world plants is a complex optimisation problem that continues to require manual intervention by experienced human operators.

item.title: The Emergence of Essential Sparsity in Large Pre-trained Models: The Weights that Matter
item.description: Large pre-trained transformers are show-stealer in modern-day deep learning, and it becomes crucial to comprehend the parsimonious patterns that exist within them as they grow in scale.

item.title: CiT-Net: Convolutional Neural Networks Hand in Hand with Vision Transformers for Medical Image Segmentation
item.description: The hybrid architecture of convolutional neural networks (CNNs) and Transformer are very popular for medical image segmentation.

item.title: Student Classroom Behavior Detection based on Improved YOLOv7
item.description: Accurately detecting student behavior in classroom videos can aid in analyzing their classroom performance and improving teaching effectiveness.

item.title: SciCap+: A Knowledge Augmented Dataset to Study the Challenges of Scientific Figure Captioning
item.description: Automating figure caption generation helps move model understandings of scientific documents beyond text and will help authors write informative captions that facilitate communicating scientific findings.

item.title: Curriculum-Based Augmented Fourier Domain Adaptation for Robust Medical Image Segmentation
item.description: Accurate and robust medical image segmentation is fundamental and crucial for enhancing the autonomy of computer-aided diagnosis and intervention systems.

item.title: Efficient and Interpretable Compressive Text Summarisation with Unsupervised Dual-Agent Reinforcement Learning
item.description: Recently, compressive text summarisation offers a balance between the conciseness issue of extractive summarisation and the factual hallucination issue of abstractive summarisation.

item.title: Human-Object Interaction Prediction in Videos through Gaze Following
item.description: Understanding the human-object interactions (HOIs) from a video is essential to fully comprehend a visual scene.

item.title: Learning-Based Heuristic for Combinatorial Optimization of the Minimum Dominating Set Problem using Graph Convolutional Networks
item.description: The minimum dominating set problem seeks to find a dominating set of minimum cardinality and is a well-established NP-hard combinatorial optimization problem.

item.title: Supervised Knowledge May Hurt Novel Class Discovery Performance
item.description: Next, by using the proposed transfer flow, we conduct various empirical experiments with different levels of semantic similarity, yielding that supervised knowledge may hurt NCD performance.

item.title: FAMO: Fast Adaptive Multitask Optimization
item.description: One of the grand enduring goals of AI is to create generalist agents that can learn multiple different tasks from diverse data via multitask learning (MTL).

item.title: Take the Hint: Improving Arabic Diacritization with Partially-Diacritized Text
item.description: Automatic Arabic diacritization is useful in many applications, ranging from reading support for language learners to accurate pronunciation predictor for downstream tasks like speech synthesis.

item.title: Masked Autoencoders are Efficient Continual Federated Learners
item.description: In parts, federated learning lifts this assumption, as it sets out to solve the real-world challenge of collaboratively learning a shared model from data distributed across clients.

item.title: Deductive Verification of Chain-of-Thought Reasoning
item.description: In light of this, we propose to decompose a reasoning verification process into a series of step-by-step subprocesses, each only receiving their necessary context and premises.

item.title: Inference-Time Intervention: Eliciting Truthful Answers from a Language Model
item.description: This intervention significantly improves the performance of LLaMA models on the TruthfulQA benchmark.

item.title: Learning Dynamical Systems from Noisy Data with Inverse-Explicit Integrators
item.description: We introduce the mean inverse integrator (MII), a novel approach to increase the accuracy when training neural networks to approximate vector fields of dynamical systems from noisy data.

item.title: Machine learning in and out of equilibrium
item.description: In an example system where the posterior is exactly known, this SGWORLD algorithm outperforms SGLD, converging to the posterior orders of magnitude faster as a function of the learning rate.

item.title: Memory-Based Dual Gaussian Processes for Sequential Learning
item.description: Sequential learning with Gaussian processes (GPs) is challenging when access to past data is limited, for example, in continual and active learning.

item.title: ColdNAS: Search to Modulate for User Cold-Start Recommendation
item.description: Instead of using a fixed modulation function and deciding modulation position by expertise, we propose a modulation framework called ColdNAS for user cold-start problem, where we look for proper modulation structure, including function and position, via neural architecture search.

item.title: Agents Explore the Environment Beyond Good Actions to Improve Their Model for Better Decisions
item.description: To improve the planning skills needed to make good decisions, MuZero's agent combines prediction by a network model and planning by a tree search using the predictions.

item.title: On the Difference of BERT-style and CLIP-style Text Encoders
item.description: Masked language modeling (MLM) has been one of the most popular pretraining recipes in natural language processing, e. g., BERT, one of the representative models.

item.title: From Key Points to Key Point Hierarchy: Structured and Expressive Opinion Summarization
item.description: Key Point Analysis (KPA) has been recently proposed for deriving fine-grained insights from collections of textual comments.

item.title: A Cross-Linguistic Pressure for Uniform Information Density in Word Order
item.description: Here, we ask whether a pressure for UID may have influenced word order patterns cross-linguistically.

item.title: I'm Afraid I Can't Do That: Predicting Prompt Refusal in Black-Box Generative Language Models
item.description: With this machine-labeled data, we train a prompt classifier to predict whether ChatGPT will refuse a given question, without seeing ChatGPT's response.

item.title: SGAT4PASS: Spherical Geometry-Aware Transformer for PAnoramic Semantic Segmentation
item.description: Experimental results on Stanford2D3D Panoramic datasets show that SGAT4PASS significantly improves performance and robustness, with approximately a 2% increase in mIoU, and when small 3D disturbances occur in the data, the stability of our performance is improved by an order of magnitude.

item.title: DVIS: Decoupled Video Instance Segmentation Framework
item.description: The efficacy of the decoupling strategy relies on two crucial elements: 1) attaining precise long-term alignment outcomes via frame-by-frame association during tracking, and 2) the effective utilization of temporal information predicated on the aforementioned accurate alignment outcomes during refinement.

item.title: Towards Alleviating the Object Bias in Prompt Tuning-based Factual Knowledge Extraction
item.description: Many works employed prompt tuning methods to automatically optimize prompt queries and extract the factual knowledge stored in Pretrained Language Models.

item.title: GEO-Bench: Toward Foundation Models for Earth Monitoring
item.description: Recent progress in self-supervision has shown that pre-training large neural networks on vast amounts of unsupervised data can lead to substantial increases in generalization to downstream tasks.

item.title: SAM3D: Segment Anything in 3D Scenes
item.description: In this work, we propose SAM3D, a novel framework that is able to predict masks in 3D point clouds by leveraging the Segment-Anything Model (SAM) in RGB images without further training or finetuning.

item.title: Simulation-Based Counterfactual Causal Discovery on Real World Driver Behaviour
item.description: Being able to reason about how one's behaviour can affect the behaviour of others is a core skill required of intelligent driving agents.
